  <item>
    <title>Running Helios as a desktop app</title>
    <link>http://nicolas-petton.fr/blog/nw-helios.html#sec-1</link>
    <author>Nicolas Petton</author>
    <guid isPermaLink="false">http://nicolas-petton.fr/blog/nw-helios.html#sec-1</guid>
    <pubDate>Thu, 03 Apr 2014 11:17:00 +0200</pubDate>
    <category><![CDATA[amber]]></category>
    <description><![CDATA[
    <div class="pubdate">
    April 3, 2014
    </div>

    <p>
    I just pushed on the <a href="https://github.com/amber-smalltalk/amber/tree/nw-helios-app">nw-helios-app</a> branch a working version of
    Helios running as a desktop app, remotely connected to an Amber app.
    </p>


    <div class="figure">
    <p><img src="http://nicolas-petton.fr/blog/../images/nw-helios.png" alt="niflheim" />  
    </p>
    <p><span class="figure-number">Figure 1:</span> Niflheim theme</p>
    </div>

    <p>
    To try it yourself, you&rsquo;ll first need to install <a href="https://github.com/rogerwang/node-webkit">node-webkit</a> then
    run from the `hw-helios-app` branch:
    </p>

    <div class="bash">
    <p>
    nw helios.nw
    </p>

    </div>

